| clazz = com.fluidops.iwb.widget.TabWidget
}}


==== Simple Example: show the Help:Start and :MyPage as tabs ====

<source>
{{#widget: TabWidget | 
 includes = {{ 
      {{ pageUri = 'Help:Start'
       | tooltip = 'This is the tooltip for Help:Start'
       | title = 'Help:Start'
      }} | 
      {{ pageUri = ':MyPage'
       | title = 'My Page'
      }} }}
}}
</source>

==== Styling of tab widget ====

The Tab Widget supports styling rules to adjust its appearance. Consider for example the use case, when all tabs represent tables (i.e., the only content of a tab is a [[Help:TableResult| table result widget]]). When applying the css class ''tabbedTable'' on the widget, the table appears connected to the tab menu.

<source>
{{#widget: TabWidget | 
 includes = {{ 
      {{ pageUri = ':PageWithTable1'
       | title = 'Table1 1'
      }} | 
      {{ pageUri = ':PageWithTable2'
       | title = 'Table 2'
      }} }}
 | styling = 
   {{ cssClass = 'tabbedTable'
   }}
}}
</source>

In addition it is possible to define the CSS classes ''noTableTab'' and ''tableTab'' on the individual tab containers to use mixed rendering.